v. adjudicated, adjudicating, adjudicates
v.tr.
1. To hear and settle (a case) by judicial procedure.
2. To study and settle (a dispute or conflict).
v.intr.
To act as a judge.
[Latin adidicre, adidict-, to award to (judicially) : ad-, ad- + idicre, to judge (from idex, judge; see judge).]
adjudication n.
adjudicative adj.
adjudicator n.